data.value:
Created for the class Software Practice I at the University of Utah.
How to use Spreadsheet Creator:
- Below the menu bar is where you can view and edit the contents and values of a cell. - When editing the contents, you may either click the enter button on the right to submit or press 'Enter' on your keyboard. - You may hold Shift and click on a cell to automatically add its cell name to the contents instead of typing it out.
Hero Mode:
- Hero Mode is an exciting new feature that is the future of spreadsheet making. - Adds a level of excitement, difficulty, and risk to the spreadsheet creation process. - In this mode the spreadsheet can only be saved once and if you make a mistake and enter an invalid formula the entire application exit and your single save deleted.
Jukebox:
-The jukebox can turn what would normally be a boring silent spreadsheet in an engaging orchestra of sound. -To operate the jukebox simply press the "Open" button to begin playing.
